(392, 1, '2018-07-20 16:45:54', '2018-07-20 16:45:54', '<div class="small">Popbox.js is a tiny javascript plugin for creating stackable modals</div>\r\n<div class="small">It is fully customizable and dependency free.</div>\r\n<div class="card_content"><button data-popbox-target="modal1">Open Popbox Modal</button>\r\n<pre><code>\r\n						<strong>Installation</strong>\r\n						\r\n						\r\n</code></pre>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style="list-style-type: none">\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Add the popbox.css file to the head of your html.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style="list-style-type: none">\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Add the popbox.js file to the head of your html or right before the closing body tag.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style="list-style-type: none">\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Add this code after the popbox.js script tag to initialize the plugin.\r\n<textarea disabled="disabled">								&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;\r\n									var popbox = &nbsp; new Popbox({\r\n										&nbsp; &nbsp;	blur:true,\r\n										&nbsp; });\r\n								&lt;/script&gt;\r\n							</textarea></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<pre><code></code></pre>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<pre><code></code></pre>\r\n<pre><code>\r\n						<strong>Example html</strong>\r\n						\r\n						\r\n							<textarea style="min-height: 550px;" disabled="disabled">								&nbsp; &lt;div data-popbox-id="mypopbox1" class="popbox"&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &lt;div class="popbox_container"&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &nbsp;	Popbox content 1\r\n									&nbsp; &nbsp;	&lt;button data-popbox-close="mypopbox1"&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &lt;/div&gt;\r\n								&nbsp; &lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n								&nbsp; &lt;div data-popbox-id="mypopbox2" class="popbox"&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &lt;div class="popbox_container"&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &nbsp;	Popbox content 2\r\n									&nbsp; &lt;/div&gt;\r\n									&nbsp; &nbsp;	&lt;button data-popbox-close="mypopbox2"&gt;Close&lt;/button&gt;\r\n	