(469, 1, '2019-09-16 21:02:39', '2019-09-16 21:02:39', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What it does:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Displays Instagram posts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In future will add ability to display Twitter and YouTube posts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How to use:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Install plugin</li><li>Plugin creates a post type: rc_social_post</li><li>Go to Settings &gt; RC Social Posts to set the Instagram username and number of posts to show. Recommended to keep divisible by 12 so Bootstrap columns work with short code</li><li> Cron job pulls in new Instagram posts and creates posts under rc_social_post </li><li> Go to Dashboard and click button "Refresh Feed" to see Instagram posts right away </li><li>Will show up as one row of images if you use shortcode [instagram-posts]</li><li>To display posts differently - either add more functionality to the shortcode or loop through post type rc_social_post inside your theme</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Future Additions</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Twitter and YouTube Functionality</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Required</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Install <a href="http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/25/github-updater/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="GitHub Updater (opens in a new tab)">GitHub Updater</a> with this plugin, so updates to the master branch get pushed to the website </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:button -->\n<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/plugin-social_posts/src/master/">Get repo</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button -->', 'Social Posts', '<p><strong>What it does:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Displays Instagram posts.</p>\n\n<p>In future will add ability to display Twitter and YouTube posts.</p>\n\n<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/plugin-social_posts/src/master/">Get repo</a></div>', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'social-posts', '', '', '2019-09-30 18:13:39', '2019-09-30 18:13:39', '', 0, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/?p=469', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(479, 1, '2019-09-16 21:11:14', '2019-09-16 21:11:14', 'You can post a JS message to the parent page using window.parent.postMessage() function. I didn\'t know this was possible. <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/postMessage" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Developer Mozilla window post message</a>\r\n\r\nCan be used to interact between the windows. There is security concerns with this if the targetOrigin parameter is not set to the target with this function.', 'Posting Message From An Embed or iFrame to Parent Page', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '341-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:11:14', '2019-09-16 21:11:14', '', 341, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/341-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(480, 1, '2019-09-16 21:11:27', '2019-09-16 21:11:27', 'In the <a href="https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/divi-child-them" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">divi child theme </a>there is a modal menu on the mobile view. You can see it on the <a href="http://divi.rcdesign.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RC divi boilerplates site</a>.\r\nThe Files in use are:\r\nPHP: header.php, template-parts/mobile-menu.php\r\nJS: menu.js\r\nCSS: _header.scss, and _modal.scss\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-334" src="http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Screen-Shot-2017-11-20-at-2.49.54-PM-300x88.png" alt="" width="300" height="88" />\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-335" src="http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/Screen-Shot-2017-11-20-at-2.49.59-PM-300x113.png" alt="" width="300" height="113" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Divi Child Theme Modal Menu', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '330-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:11:27', '2019-09-16 21:11:27', '', 330, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/330-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(481, 1, '2019-09-16 21:13:15', '2019-09-16 21:13:15', 'Here is a <a href="https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/divi-child-theme/downloads/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Divid Child Theme Skeleton</a>. Divi will run fine with this child theme activated as is. However there are two items missing from a normal RC theme. A <a href="https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/annas-flowers/raw/94c5fc6f6319bed4b2744b02bc3073b13699141e/gulpfile.js" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" download>gulpfile</a> and an assets folder. The package.json is already included to install the <em>npm</em> for gulp.', 'Divi Child Theme Skeleton Template', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '320-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:13:15', '2019-09-16 21:13:15', '', 320, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/320-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(482, 1, '2019-09-16 21:14:07', '2019-09-16 21:14:07', '<iframe aysync src="//jsfiddle.net/nk74x8ro/8/embedded/result,html/" width="100%" height="300" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\r\n\r\nRequires jquery, bootstrap CSS and JS.\r\nHTML\r\n<pre>\r\n//button\r\n<a class="privacy-button a" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#privacyModal" rel="noopener noreferrer">Privacy Policy</a>\r\n\r\n//modal\r\n<div id="privacyModal" class="modal fade rc-modal container" role="dialog" style="display: none;" aria-hidden="true">\r\n  <div class="modal-dialog">\r\n\r\n    <!-- Modal content-->\r\n    <div class="modal-content">\r\n      <a type="" class="close rc-modal" data-dismiss="modal" tabindex="0" data-target="#teamModal" rel="noopener noreferrer">\r\n        <i class="fa fa-times" aria-hidden="true"></i>\r\n      </a>\r\n      <div class="modal-body">\r\n      </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</pre>', 'Bootstrap Modal Basic Setup', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '293-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:14:07', '2019-09-16 21:14:07', '', 293, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/293-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(483, 1, '2019-09-16 21:16:18', '2019-09-16 21:16:18', '<pre>function wpb_new_contactmethods( $contactmethods ) {\r\n// Add Twitter\r\n$contactmethods[\'twitter\'] = \'Twitter\';\r\n//add Facebook\r\n$contactmethods[\'facebook\'] = \'Facebook\';\r\n\r\nreturn $contactmethods;\r\n}\r\nadd_filter(\'user_contactmethods\',\'wpb_new_contactmethods\',10,1);</pre>\r\n\r\nFind our more tips and tricks - 32 Extremely Useful Tricks for the WordPress Functions File: <a href="http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/25-extremely-useful-tricks-for-the-wordpress-functions-file/" target="_blkank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/25-extremely-useful-tricks-for-the-wordpress-functions-file/</a>\r\n\r\n', 'WordPress - Add Author Profile Fields', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '256-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:16:18', '2019-09-16 21:16:18', '', 256, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/256-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(484, 1, '2019-09-16 21:18:46', '2019-09-16 21:18:46', '<pre>add_action(\'wp_dashboard_setup\', \'my_custom_dashboard_widgets\');\r\n\r\nfunction my_custom_dashboard_widgets() {\r\nglobal $wp_meta_boxes;\r\n\r\nwp_add_dashboard_widget(\'custom_help_widget\', \'Theme Support\', \'custom_dashboard_help\');\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction custom_dashboard_help() {\r\necho \'<p>Welcome to Custom Blog Theme! Need help? Contact the developer <a href="mailto:yourusername@gmail.com">here</a>. For a custom website visit: <a href="http://www.rcdesign.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">RC Design</a></p>\';\r\n}</pre>', 'Add Custom Dashboard Widgets in WordPress', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '254-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:18:46', '2019-09-16 21:18:46', '', 254, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/254-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(485, 1, '2019-09-16 21:19:26', '2019-09-16 21:19:26', 'Make Bootstrap Columns All the Same Height\r\n\r\n<strong>HTML:</strong>\r\n<pre><div class="container">\r\n    <div class="row is-flex">\r\n        <div class="col-sm-4">\r\n            <div class="box">\r\n                <h2>Title</h2>\r\n                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor.</p>\r\n                <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Link 1</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="col-sm-4">\r\n            <div class="box">\r\n                <h2>Title</h2>\r\n                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor.</p>\r\n                <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Link 2</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class="col-sm-4">\r\n            <div class="box">\r\n                <h2>Ttitle</h2>\r\n                <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt.</p>\r\n                <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Link 3</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div></pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>CSS:</strong>\r\n<pre>.row.is-flex {\r\n  display: -webkit-box;\r\n  display: -webkit-flex;\r\n  display: -ms-flexbox;\r\n  display: flex;\r\n  flex-wrap: wrap;\r\n}\r\n.row.is-flex > [class*=\'col-\'] {\r\n  display: -webkit-box;\r\n  display: -webkit-flex;\r\n  display: -ms-flexbox;\r\n  display: flex;\r\n  flex-direction: column;\r\n}\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>Solution 2 using table</strong>\r\n\r\n<pre>.row {\r\n    display: table;\r\n}\r\n\r\n[class*="col-"] {\r\n    float: none;\r\n    display: table-cell;\r\n    vertical-align: top;\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\nMore Different Tricks on How to Make Bootstrap Columns All the Same Height: <a href="https://scotch.io/bar-talk/different-tricks-on-how-to-make-bootstrap-columns-all-the-same-height" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://scotch.io/bar-talk/different-tricks-on-how-to-make-bootstrap-columns-all-the-same-height</a>', 'Flexbox - the same columns height', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '246-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-16 21:19:26', '2019-09-16 21:19:26', '', 246, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/16/246-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
