(495, 1, '2019-09-16 22:11:20', '2019-09-16 22:11:20', '<!-- wp:html -->\n<p>Go to Wordpress live website and download database using Migrate DB (Tools &gt; Migrate DB). Install if not there.</p>\n<p>The database will have the production URL populated in the Find column, in the Replace column enter your local URL (//website.local). Then download the database. Rename file to backup.sql and put in your websites files under {project_name}/app</p>\n<p>Open Local by Flywheel and start your website. Right click again and find "Open Site SSH" and click. A terminal will open. Enter this code and press enter:</p>\n<pre>mysql -u root -proot -f local &lt; /app/backup.sql</pre>\n<p>And you\'re done!</p>\n<p>See this article for more details: https://www.ibenic.com/import-databases-local-flywheel-sites/</p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->', 'Import large SQL files into Flywheel Local', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'import-large-sql-files-into-flywheel-local', '', '', '2019-09-26 18:45:35', '2019-09-26 18:45:35', '', 0, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/?p=495', 0, 'post', '', 0),
