>, its directory and file structure should look something like this:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class="wp-block-code"><code> good-plugin.php\n readme.txt\n README.md\n CHANGES.md\n includes\n|     ...\n|     queries.php\n ...\n ...</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Plugins</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There must be a&nbsp;<code>GitHub Plugin URI</code>,&nbsp;<code>Bitbucket Plugin URI</code>,&nbsp;<code>GitLab Plugin URI</code>, or&nbsp;<code>Gitea Plugin URI</code>&nbsp;declaration in the plugin\'s header.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">/**\n Plugin Name:       Plugin Social Posts\n Plugin URI:        https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/plugin-social_posts\n Description:       Demonstrates how to write custom administration pages in WordPress.\n Version:           1.0.0\n Author:            Ben Ross\n Text Domain:       plugin-social-posts\n Bitbucket Plugin URI: https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/plugin-social_posts\n */ </pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3><a href="https://github.com/afragen/github-updater/wiki/Usage#themes"></a>Themes</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There must be a&nbsp;<code>GitHub Theme URI</code>,&nbsp;<code>Bitbucket Theme URI</code>,&nbsp;<code>GitLab Theme URI</code>, or&nbsp;<code>Gitea Theme URI</code>&nbsp;declaration in the&nbsp;<code>style.css</code>&nbsp;file. When initially adding a theme, the directory&nbsp;<strong>must</strong>&nbsp;be identical to the repo name.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:preformatted -->\n<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">/**\n * Theme Name:          SouthLake\n * Version:             1.0.0\n * Description:         Child theme of framework.\n * Author:              RC Design\n * Author URI:          https://rcdesign.com\n * Template:            framework\n * Bitbucket Theme URI: https://bitbucket.org/rcdesigninc/southlake\n */</pre>\n<!-- /wp:preformatted -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->\n<h3>Bitbucket Support</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead of the&nbsp;<code>GitHub Plugin URI</code>&nbsp;header you will need to use the&nbsp;<code>Bitbucket Plugin URI</code>&nbsp;header.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Instead of the&nbsp;<code>GitHub Theme URI</code>&nbsp;header you will need to use the&nbsp;<code>Bitbucket Theme URI</code>&nbsp;header.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:button -->\n<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="https://github.com/afragen/github-updater">Get repo</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button -->', 'GitHub Updater', '<p><strong>What it does:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Allows us to push changes of our plugins installed on client websites.</p>\n\n<div class="wp-block-button"><a class="wp-block-button__link" href="https://github.com/afragen/github-updater">Get repo</a></div>', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '614-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-09-26 15:07:26', '2019-09-26 15:07:26', '', 614, 'http://wiki.christinewilson.ca/2019/09/26/614-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
